        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. According to WHO 1999 'Concise International Chemical Assessment Document 16 AZODICARBONAMIDE' little information is disclosed about production volume of azodicarbonamide. For the year 1996 the production volume of the US was greater then 4.54 tonnes. Additionally they report that the UK stopped producting this product and started importing a quantity of 2500 tonnes. 

According to Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry, the global annual consumption of blowing agents is circa 15 000 tonnes. Azodicarbonamide is by far the most important product. 

The production volume is therefore estimated to be 80% of blowing agent production.


Placeholder is scaled from the Global production volume which is set to 4. 
According to Cefic (2016) the Global sales of chemicals in the year 2015 was 3,534 billion euros. The reported share of sales per regions are: EU28 14.7%; Other Europe (Switzerland, Norway, Turkey, Russia and Ukraine) 2.7%; NAFTA (USA, Canada and Mexico) 16.5%; Latin America 3.8%; China 39.9%; Japan 3.9%; Republic of Korea 3.2%; India 2.2%; Rest of Asia 11.9%; Rest of the World 1.3%. Cefic also reports the USA total sales, 518.7 billion euros of the global 3534 billion euros (14.7%). The same share is reported from the American Chemistry Council (2016), according to this source the USA sales account for 15% of global sales for the year 2016. 
The EU production volume is calculated based on the sales share from RER, which is here defined as EU28 plus Other Europe, share of sales (14.7% + 2.7% = 17.4% of global).

Reference(s):
Cefic 2016. Facts and figures 2016 of the European chemical industry. Accessible at: http://www.cefic.org/Facts-and-Figures/Chemicals-Industry-Profile/ 
American Chemistry Council 2016. Outlook: U.S. Chemical Industry Continues to Outpace Industrial Output; Accounts for More Than One-Half of Construction Spending by Manufacturing Sector. Accessible at: https://www.americanchemistry.com/Media/PressReleasesTranscripts/ACC-news-releases/US-Chemical-Industry-Continues-to-Outpace-Industrial-Output.html
Wolf, R. and Kaul, B. L. 2000. Plastics, Additives. Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry. </productionVolumeComment>
